<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The getParam() and getParams() have duplicate methods called getUserParam() and getUserParams(), respectively. Looking at their definition, they do the same exact thing, which almost the same exact code defined twice. If anything, the getUser* methods should just be aliases, if not removed altogether. It would help to reduce the overall code complexity, and alleviate any confusion for users (i.e., why are there two sets of methods that imply different results, but do the same things?)</p>

    </div>
